OL,3,CCoin minted in Scotland almost 900
OL,4,Cyears ago to be preserved for nation
OL,6,FThe earliest known coin minted in
OL,7,FScotland nearly 900 years ago has been
OL,8,Facquired by the nation, following its
OL,9,Fdiscovery by a metal detectorist.
OL,11,FIt was discovered in a wooded area
OL,12,Fnear Penicuik, Midlothian, and the
OL,13,FScottish Archaeological Finds
OL,14,FAllocation Panel has now allocated the
OL,15,Fcoin to National Museums Scotland.
OL,17,FThe medieval coin dates back to the
OL,18,Frule of King David I of Scotland, who
OL,19,Fintroduced coinage to the kingdom
OL,20,Fduring his reign, which lasted between
OL,21,F1124 and 1153.
