OL,3,CCoin minted in Scotland almost 900
OL,4,Cyears ago to be preserved for nation
OL,6,FUntil the discovery of this silver
OL,7,Fcoin it was believed that the earliest
OL,8,Fcoins of King David's reign were
OL,9,Fminted in Carlisle, which he conquered
OL,10,Fin the 1130s.
OL,12,FAn inscription on the coin discovered
OL,13,Fby the metal detectorist shows,
OL,14,Fhowever, that it was minted in
OL,15,FEdinburgh. It has been dated to the
OL,16,Fsecond half of the 1130s.
OL,18,FThe coin depicts David's head on one
OL,19,Fside, and on the other bears a cross-
OL,20,Fbased design.
