OL,3,CCoin minted in Scotland almost 900
OL,4,Cyears ago to be preserved for nation
OL,6,FIt was discovered in 2023, and was
OL,7,Freported to Treasure Trove as required
OL,8,Fby law. The coin was valued at
OL,9,F#15,000, which was given to the finder
OL,10,Fas a reward.
OL,12,FDr Alice Blackwell, senior curator of
OL,13,Fmedieval archaeology and history at
OL,14,FNational Museums Scotland said:
OL,15,F"Scotland had never produced coinage
OL,16,Fbefore (the reign of David I). Any
OL,17,Fcoins that are found in Scotland
OL,18,Fbefore this date have been minted
OL,19,Felsewhere, whether that's Roman Age.
OL,20,FViking Age, or medieval coinage.
